Chapter 9: Minimal Implementation – A 2‑Agent Deployable Version

For practical deployment with minimal complexity, we propose a 2‑agent version:

· Agent 1 (Agree): A standard LLM (e.g., GPT‑4) fine‑tuned to be agreeable.
· Agent 2 (Disagree): The same base model prompted to play “Devil’s advocate” and always present counterarguments.

The stability controller uses a simple scalar friction rule:

\lambda_t = \max(0, 1 + \kappa \cdot \hat{c}_t),
\]  

where \kappa > 0 is a hyperparameter. The update becomes:

H_{t+1} = H_t + \eta (A_t^{\text{agree}} - \lambda_t A_t^{\text{disagree}}) + \xi_t.
\]  

The system requires only:

· A factual consistency checker for \hat{d}_t.
· A confidence estimator for \hat{c}_t.

This version can be implemented immediately on top of existing APIs and has been tested in preliminary experiments (see Appendix B).

